Package: chromswitch
Title: An R package for detecting chromatin state switches
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: c(person("Selin", "Jessa", email = "selinjessa@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person(c("Claudia", "L."), "Kleinman", role = "aut"))  
Description: chromswitch implements a flexible method to detect chromatin state 
    switches between samples in two biological conditions in a specific genomic
    region of interest given peaks called from ChIP-seq data.
Depends: R (>= 3.4)
Imports:
    GenomicRanges (>= 1.28.2),
    IRanges (>= 2.4.8),
    methods,
    readr(>= 1.1.1)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat
URL: https://github.com/selinj/chromswitch
BugReports: https://github.com/selinj/chromswitch/issues
biocViews: MultipleComparison, Transcription, GeneExpression,
    DifferentialPeakCalling, HistoneModification, Epigenetics,
    FunctionalGenomics
    
